node.text:
It’s been a great few days with leaders, advocates, and fun Democrats from across Clinton, Lycoming, Centre and Union counties! I’m excited about the work that everyone is putting in out here and grateful for their passion for better government and better elected officials! 

If I’m going to be in your area soon (and that’s pretty likely) shoot me a message and let’s make a better visit out of whatever trip I’m on. It’d be great to meet you and whoever you are, you’re probably more fun to hang out with than many of my colleagues, so I’m in!

From the hills over Bald Eagle State Park,
Brian & Temper

node.text:
Morning from a campsite on the mountain ridge over Bald Eagle State Park! I’m in town for a few days of meetings with Mayors, County Democrats, & engaged voters from Clinton, Union & Lycoming counties! 

Yeah I know camping is better than campaigning but the people I’m spending my time with would make even the most hardened heart smile and make the most frustrated person get to the voting booth. 

Democrats are everywhere in Pennsylvania, and so I am too! If you’re wondering when we’ll be in your area, or you want to help us set something up, check out www.Sims4Pa.com and let us know!

Time for more campfire coffee!

Five years ago today, one of the most tragic and terrifying acts of domestic terrorism against LGBTQ+ people in world history happened right here in the United States. 

My Republican colleagues tried to not even mention the attack, or the murders, in large part because the victims were almost entirely Latino and LGBTQ+. I threatened the Republican Speaker of the House that next morning and he caved. 

It’s clear looking back that I was having a hard time holding it together at the podium. I’m reminded now of Maggie Kuhn’s quote “speak your mind even if your voice shakes.”

So much needed to be said. 

“You shoot us when we kiss, you beat us when we hold hands, you hate us when we fall in love, abs you ban us from donating blood to our wounded loved ones, and there are many of them.”

LEHIGH VALLEY: I can’t think of a better way to wrap up a super busy weekend than with a truly fantastic Pride! Adrian Shanker at the Bradbury-Sullivan LGBT Community Center hosted one of the most fun Pride events ever at Lehigh Valley Pride in Allentown. 

From Timika Lane, Lori Dumas, & David Spurgeon to Malcolm Kenyatta, Maraleen Shields, Matt Tuerk, the East Penn Democratic Club and the Upper Lehigh Democratic Club, the Lehigh Valley Pride was the place to be for Democrats and people who supoort equality. It felt strong and transformative. 

Thank you to the performers, vendors, supporters, allies, and LGBTQIA+ family members who worked to make this such a special event!

COLUMBIA COUNTY: Spending time today in Bloomsburg, my alma mater, with Mayor Justin Hummel and the leaders of the Columbia County PA Democrats has been an absolutely joy!

Leaders here like Vince, Jill, Dwayne, Katie & Jess are working their tails off to elect Democrats and we’re gonna turn it up this fall for the critical 2021 election. 

With our support, I believe Josh Shapiro will be the next Governor of Pennsylvania and I hope to serve the Commonwealth by serving as his Lt. Governor. That only happens when we build on the hard work being done here and across Pennsylvania, this year!

Seeya soon and often, Columbia County!
